    "doc": "Building and Running on SAMA5D2 Xplained Ultra Evaluation Kit",
    "title": "Setting up the hardware",
    "content": "The following table shows the target hardware for the application projects. | Project Name | Board | . | sam_a5d2_xult.X sam_a5d2_xult_iar.IAR | SAMA5D2 Xplained Ultra Evaluation Kit | . |   |   | . Setting up SAMA5D2 Xplained Ultra Evaluation Kit . Addtional hardware required . | SD Card with FAT32 file system | . Setting up the SD Card . | Download harmony MPU bootstrap loader from this location | Copy the downloaded boot loader binary( boot.bin) onto the SD card | . Setting up the board . | SDMMC slot used for bootloading the application is SDMMC1 | Short jumper JP2 (DEBUG_DIS) | Connect the Debug USB port on the board to the computer using a micro USB cable | . ",
